WEBVTT

00:00:01.105 --> 00:00:02.225
Let go!

00:00:02.305 --> 00:00:04.185
Help!

00:00:04.265 --> 00:00:05.225
Let go!

00:00:06.385 --> 00:00:07.705
Jay was injured.

00:00:07.785 --> 00:00:09.865
And last night, Time was found dead.

00:00:10.465 --> 00:00:12.025
- Time's dead?
- Yes.

00:00:12.105 --> 00:00:14.025
Where were you last night?

00:00:14.105 --> 00:00:15.705
Take a look at this.

00:00:15.785 --> 00:00:16.665
You'll understand.

00:00:20.425 --> 00:00:21.985
On the day Fai died,

00:00:22.065 --> 00:00:23.385
what drug did you two trade?

00:00:24.505 --> 00:00:26.345
Find the real culprit.

00:00:26.425 --> 00:00:30.225
It may be you who dies instead.

00:00:30.305 --> 00:00:31.745
Check on Jay at the hospital.

00:00:31.825 --> 00:00:32.785
I'll stay here.

00:00:32.864 --> 00:00:34.665
Let Lieutenant Prai and Lieutenant Ken
handle this minor task.

00:00:34.745 --> 00:00:36.305
I said go, so go!

00:00:37.745 --> 00:00:40.625
Just because I pursued you first
doesn't mean you can do whatever you want.

00:00:40.705 --> 00:00:42.945
If you don't clear this up,

00:00:43.025 --> 00:00:44.505
then we don't need to talk anymore.

00:00:51.625 --> 00:00:53.425
Even if I'm not a good person,

00:00:53.505 --> 00:00:55.425
please let me love you.

00:00:55.505 --> 00:00:56.905
I love you…

00:00:57.625 --> 00:00:59.505
without needing permission too.

00:01:02.425 --> 00:01:06.145
Sneaking off to see Jay
without telling the police or anyone,

00:01:06.225 --> 00:01:08.025
is that really a good idea?

00:01:08.105 --> 00:01:09.185
Who would we even tell?

00:01:09.985 --> 00:01:11.345
Telling anyone is risky.

00:01:12.105 --> 00:01:14.105
Right now,
only three of us are left alive.

00:01:14.185 --> 00:01:16.905
Hey, don't you want to survive together?

00:01:46.865 --> 00:01:48.185
Is it true…

00:01:48.945 --> 00:01:50.905
you're shameless enough

00:01:53.785 --> 00:01:55.505
to sleep with
your best friend's boyfriend?

00:01:58.825 --> 00:02:00.065
Do you want a bite?

00:02:02.785 --> 00:02:04.585
- Whose Takoyaki is this?
- Are they the same?

00:02:06.425 --> 00:02:10.625
Is it true you told Champ
about Puifai being pregnant?

00:02:10.705 --> 00:02:12.105
It's so damn hot.

00:02:13.625 --> 00:02:16.305
Even though she begged you not to.

00:02:16.945 --> 00:02:17.905
Champ.

00:02:17.985 --> 00:02:19.225
Yeah?

00:02:19.305 --> 00:02:22.705
I… I don't really know how to say this,

00:02:23.305 --> 00:02:24.425
but…

00:02:28.065 --> 00:02:30.945
Puifai might be…

00:02:42.345 --> 00:02:43.425
What does this mean?

00:02:45.065 --> 00:02:46.585
Well,

00:02:46.665 --> 00:02:48.785
Puifai might be…

00:02:51.105 --> 00:02:52.625
pregnant.

00:02:54.505 --> 00:02:56.505
You're the quiet type of slut,

00:02:57.785 --> 00:03:00.065
dying for what belongs to your friend.

00:03:02.105 --> 00:03:04.145
But you're playing
the poor innocent victim.

00:03:05.065 --> 00:03:08.905
{\an8}Puifai having an abortion
was all part of your plan.

00:03:21.065 --> 00:03:22.745
Why is there only "Truth"?

00:03:22.825 --> 00:03:24.945
Tonkla got both Truth and Dare.

00:03:25.025 --> 00:03:26.705
Well yeah.

00:03:26.785 --> 00:03:28.465
If there was one, I'd have told you.

00:03:29.065 --> 00:03:30.145
Jay,

00:03:31.345 --> 00:03:32.465
let me ask you seriously.

00:03:33.145 --> 00:03:34.585
Those hell letters…

00:03:34.665 --> 00:03:35.785
You didn't really do it, did you?

00:03:35.865 --> 00:03:36.985
Yeah, right.

00:03:37.065 --> 00:03:38.385
Why the hell would I?

00:03:38.465 --> 00:03:40.625
Then why was it that when Tonkla died,

00:03:40.705 --> 00:03:42.745
nothing happened to you at all?

00:03:44.465 --> 00:03:46.345
Cher and I were together the whole time.

00:03:46.425 --> 00:03:48.025
It definitely wasn't us.

00:03:48.105 --> 00:03:49.505
That leaves you.

00:03:51.665 --> 00:03:53.265
You're way more suspicious than I am.

00:03:54.185 --> 00:03:56.265
Just look at all the shit
you've done to our friends.

00:03:56.345 --> 00:03:58.065
Plus, you two secretly slept together.

00:03:58.145 --> 00:04:00.425
You talk like I'm the only asshole here.

00:04:00.505 --> 00:04:01.985
What about you?

00:04:02.065 --> 00:04:04.585
Sleeping with Fai behind my back, huh?

00:04:07.265 --> 00:04:08.425
Enough, Champ.

00:04:08.945 --> 00:04:11.105
Among the three of us, none of us did it.

00:04:12.345 --> 00:04:14.625
Shouldn't we focus on surviving instead?

00:04:17.585 --> 00:04:19.825
So what are you two going to do next?

00:05:33.905 --> 00:05:34.825
Kamin.

00:06:11.625 --> 00:06:13.425
Back when you were in Special Ops?

00:06:18.585 --> 00:06:19.625
Yeah.

00:06:19.705 --> 00:06:21.545
We were investigating

00:06:21.625 --> 00:06:24.185
Seon Jae's drug
trafficking route back then.

00:06:24.265 --> 00:06:26.225
Can you stop worrying about the victim
and just stick to the plan?

00:06:27.465 --> 00:06:28.905
Kamin!

00:06:28.985 --> 00:06:30.265
Damn it!

00:06:45.025 --> 00:06:46.785
Hey!

00:06:46.865 --> 00:06:48.065
Jack!

00:06:49.585 --> 00:06:51.025
Jack!

00:06:51.105 --> 00:06:51.985
Jack!

00:06:52.665 --> 00:06:53.865
Jack!

00:06:55.545 --> 00:06:56.785
Jack!

00:06:57.545 --> 00:06:58.545
Call for backup!

00:06:58.625 --> 00:06:59.745
Jack!

00:07:00.345 --> 00:07:03.985
Honestly, the one who should've died
that day was me.

00:07:06.705 --> 00:07:08.425
So you think it's going to happen to me?

00:07:09.585 --> 00:07:12.025
The letter said

00:07:12.105 --> 00:07:14.185
we could end up dead instead.

00:07:16.065 --> 00:07:17.745
I don't want anything to happen to you.

00:07:19.145 --> 00:07:22.985
Don't forget that I'm a cop too.

00:07:23.785 --> 00:07:25.185
I can protect myself.

00:07:27.305 --> 00:07:28.745
I trust you.

00:07:30.105 --> 00:07:32.185
But I just don't trust myself.

00:07:33.705 --> 00:07:35.865
As long as you're still on this case,

00:07:36.545 --> 00:07:39.385
I'm not sure if I can focus 100%.

00:07:42.745 --> 00:07:44.425
Please withdraw from it.

00:07:49.745 --> 00:07:51.145
No matter what you say,

00:07:53.865 --> 00:07:57.545
you need to understand
that I have my duty too.

00:07:58.985 --> 00:08:02.065
I'm not the kind of cop who just sits back

00:08:03.145 --> 00:08:05.305
and lets criminals toy with us.

00:08:15.465 --> 00:08:17.385
Then I'm ordering you, as your superior.

00:08:19.505 --> 00:08:21.145
Take some time off.

00:08:23.105 --> 00:08:25.065
I don't want to be the one
who has to transfer you.

00:08:25.145 --> 00:08:26.545
Inspector.

00:08:28.105 --> 00:08:30.505
Don't pull rank on me.

00:08:30.585 --> 00:08:34.945
I won't follow orders
that don't make sense.

00:08:38.144 --> 00:08:40.625
And don't tell me to leave this case.

00:08:40.705 --> 00:08:42.904
I won't let you face this alone.

00:09:03.705 --> 00:09:04.785
Oh, hey.

00:09:05.945 --> 00:09:07.705
You're not waiting to go together?

00:09:10.105 --> 00:09:11.465
I need to hurry to work.

00:09:12.265 --> 00:09:16.305
A subordinate like me shouldn't be late,

00:09:16.385 --> 00:09:17.385
or my superior will scold me.

00:09:27.665 --> 00:09:29.225
Hello, Mirin.

00:09:34.665 --> 00:09:35.545
Yes.

00:09:37.225 --> 00:09:38.665
Come with me today.

00:09:39.545 --> 00:09:42.945
We've got an updated report
on Seon Jae's drug buyers

00:09:43.665 --> 00:09:46.385
and a lead that could get us
to the culprit.

00:09:47.985 --> 00:09:50.185
Are you updating me as my inspector

00:09:51.385 --> 00:09:52.785
or as my boyfriend?

00:09:55.785 --> 00:09:57.065
As your boyfriend.

00:10:09.025 --> 00:10:10.905
Stop sulking, will you?

00:10:26.585 --> 00:10:29.825
After reviewing the transaction records
of people dealing drugs with Seon Jae,

00:10:29.905 --> 00:10:33.505
we couldn't trace them any further.

00:10:34.305 --> 00:10:36.865
Most of them are foreigners.

00:10:36.945 --> 00:10:41.945
But Manmai dug a little deeper
and found one name.

00:10:42.585 --> 00:10:44.025
- All right.
- Here you are.

00:10:44.105 --> 00:10:47.305
This person transferred money
to Seon Jae several times,

00:10:47.385 --> 00:10:48.585
always in the same amount.

00:10:50.665 --> 00:10:52.825
So that means a regular customer.

00:10:52.905 --> 00:10:55.105
Normally, the transfers are done
via crypto,

00:10:55.185 --> 00:10:57.185
since it can't be traced to an identity.

00:10:57.265 --> 00:11:00.545
But there was one time where
the amount was the same as the others,

00:11:00.625 --> 00:11:02.625
but it came from an account
under the name Chayamporn.

00:11:02.705 --> 00:11:03.945
That's Champ.

00:11:05.545 --> 00:11:09.025
So we can confirm for sure
that this is Champ's account, right?

00:11:09.105 --> 00:11:10.625
Yes, absolutely.

00:11:10.705 --> 00:11:14.985
Even though the transfer records
could put Champ under investigation,

00:11:15.065 --> 00:11:17.705
but if he gets a good lawyer,

00:11:17.785 --> 00:11:19.345
he'll get away with it

00:11:19.425 --> 00:11:22.865
since we still don't have
solid supporting evidence.

00:11:23.625 --> 00:11:26.865
But if we arrest Champ and get his phone,

00:11:26.945 --> 00:11:29.825
we should be able to get much stronger
evidence of the drug transactions.

00:11:29.905 --> 00:11:31.345
Thank you.

00:11:34.825 --> 00:11:37.905
Please put together a summary report
for me as well. Thanks.

00:11:37.985 --> 00:11:39.225
Sure.

00:11:39.305 --> 00:11:40.465
Yes.

00:11:46.665 --> 00:11:49.545
Rin, do you think those two are sulking?

00:11:49.625 --> 00:11:51.385
The atmosphere feels really tense.

00:11:52.025 --> 00:11:53.065
How could it not be?

00:11:53.145 --> 00:11:55.705
{\an8}FORENSICS

00:11:59.105 --> 00:12:00.225
Jade.

00:12:02.425 --> 00:12:03.905
What is it, Inspector?

00:12:04.665 --> 00:12:06.585
Can we not be like this?

00:12:07.705 --> 00:12:09.265
We're at work.

00:12:09.345 --> 00:12:10.585
I don't discuss personal matters on duty.

00:12:11.185 --> 00:12:12.625
Let's talk this through.

00:12:13.505 --> 00:12:16.265
I want you to know that
I told you to take time off

00:12:17.345 --> 00:12:18.665
because I'm worried about you.

00:12:23.905 --> 00:12:25.305
So you're the only one allowed to worry?

00:12:25.385 --> 00:12:27.465
I don't have the right to worry?

00:12:35.505 --> 00:12:36.865
What?

00:12:37.865 --> 00:12:39.065
What are you doing?

00:12:39.705 --> 00:12:41.145
Where are you taking me?

00:12:42.225 --> 00:12:43.305
Inspector!

00:12:52.545 --> 00:12:53.985
Harder!

00:12:55.505 --> 00:12:57.505
You like boxing, don't you?

00:12:57.585 --> 00:12:58.905
Is that all the strength you've got?

00:12:58.985 --> 00:13:00.865
How I punch is my business.

00:13:04.065 --> 00:13:05.905
Come on. More force.

00:13:06.585 --> 00:13:08.505
Hit harder.

00:13:09.665 --> 00:13:12.185
The harder it is,
the more stress it relieves, right?

00:13:12.785 --> 00:13:15.105
You're the one who's stressed, not me.

00:13:18.585 --> 00:13:19.945
Dodge.

00:13:20.785 --> 00:13:22.225
So what?

00:13:22.305 --> 00:13:24.785
This is how you're trying
to get me to stop being mad?

00:13:24.865 --> 00:13:26.465
Well? Are you over it?

00:13:33.545 --> 00:13:34.865
No.

00:13:39.385 --> 00:13:40.865
But it's kind of cute.

00:13:42.825 --> 00:13:44.025
Come on.

00:13:45.425 --> 00:13:46.665
Go.

00:13:47.305 --> 00:13:48.305
Dodge.

00:13:52.865 --> 00:13:54.105
Not bad at all.

00:14:01.905 --> 00:14:02.985
Inspector,

00:14:05.185 --> 00:14:06.945
I know you're worried about me.

00:14:09.825 --> 00:14:12.345
But I want you to understand
that your ex-subordinate and I…

00:14:12.425 --> 00:14:14.265
are not the same person.

00:14:18.945 --> 00:14:21.025
I know loss could trigger you.

00:14:24.825 --> 00:14:27.145
But I want you to know
you're not at fault.

00:14:29.905 --> 00:14:31.345
I want you to move on.

00:14:37.145 --> 00:14:38.305
Can you?

00:14:42.705 --> 00:14:43.865
Yeah.

00:14:48.705 --> 00:14:50.225
Come on.

00:14:50.305 --> 00:14:51.585
One more round.

00:14:56.705 --> 00:14:57.585
Inspector!

00:14:58.665 --> 00:15:00.545
Ouch!

00:15:31.305 --> 00:15:33.545
Is this how you usually
make up with people?

00:15:38.425 --> 00:15:40.025
I rarely make up with anyone.

00:15:42.145 --> 00:15:43.785
So I'm your first, huh?

00:15:43.865 --> 00:15:45.625
Don't get cocky.

00:15:47.785 --> 00:15:49.505
If I sulk someday,

00:15:49.585 --> 00:15:51.185
how are you going to make it up to me?

00:15:52.745 --> 00:15:54.545
I'll have my own way.

00:15:56.865 --> 00:15:58.865
And you think I'll forgive you?

00:15:58.945 --> 00:16:02.265
Someone like you is so easy to read.

00:16:03.705 --> 00:16:05.985
Arguing back like this means

00:16:08.265 --> 00:16:10.065
you're not sulking anymore, right?

00:16:14.945 --> 00:16:16.345
I won't be

00:16:21.185 --> 00:16:22.785
if I get more than this.

00:16:27.345 --> 00:16:28.545
At home.

00:16:43.865 --> 00:16:45.425
You're asking for it.

00:16:49.785 --> 00:16:50.985
Take care of it, okay?

00:16:54.345 --> 00:16:58.105
The officer watching Jay said he secretly
went to see Cherreen and Champ.

00:16:58.185 --> 00:17:00.305
The kid played dumb
and said he knew nothing.

00:17:00.385 --> 00:17:03.385
- Let's go to the hospital. Forget about--
- Let's put Jay's issue on hold for now.

00:17:07.025 --> 00:17:09.265
We've found Seon Jae's hideout.

00:17:09.345 --> 00:17:11.224
If we arrest Seon Jae,

00:17:11.305 --> 00:17:12.825
we can nail the culprit.

00:17:15.585 --> 00:17:18.184
Seon Jae is about to leave the country.

00:17:19.184 --> 00:17:20.665
What?

00:17:20.745 --> 00:17:22.704
Seon Jae is about to leave the country.

00:17:23.385 --> 00:17:25.184
If we let him get away,

00:17:26.105 --> 00:17:27.704
we'll never know
who he's been supplying the drugs to.

00:17:28.785 --> 00:17:32.225
Inspector, don't stop me
from working on this case.

00:17:32.825 --> 00:17:35.065
Like you'd listen if I did.

00:17:37.505 --> 00:17:38.825
Then stay close to me.

00:17:43.745 --> 00:17:45.185
- Shall we go now?
- Let's go.

00:17:58.225 --> 00:18:03.905
Do we really have to go to your house
in another province?

00:18:05.905 --> 00:18:08.665
We could ask Jay's brother
for help instead.

00:18:09.705 --> 00:18:13.625
And wait for the cops to grill you
about what you did to Fai, huh?

00:18:13.705 --> 00:18:16.385
I told you I'll handle it myself.

00:18:18.105 --> 00:18:20.425
Champ, you really haven't received
the letter, have you?

00:18:32.145 --> 00:18:34.585
And if the letter told you to kill me,

00:18:35.985 --> 00:18:37.465
would you do it?

00:18:46.905 --> 00:18:50.505
Why ask when you already know the answer?

00:18:51.745 --> 00:18:54.785
Hey, don't you trust me anymore?

00:18:59.025 --> 00:19:00.465
I do trust you,

00:19:02.505 --> 00:19:04.625
but I just want reassurance.

00:19:06.025 --> 00:19:07.785
Then don't worry.

00:19:07.865 --> 00:19:08.785
I'll protect you.

00:19:10.665 --> 00:19:13.025
I'm sorry for snapping at you earlier.

00:19:13.625 --> 00:19:15.105
Shall we go?

00:19:16.865 --> 00:19:17.705
Let's go.

00:19:19.865 --> 00:19:21.225
After you.

00:19:43.065 --> 00:19:44.665
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

00:19:45.305 --> 00:19:46.465
What is it?

00:19:47.425 --> 00:19:49.025
Another mysterious letter?

00:19:50.745 --> 00:19:52.145
I searched it online.

00:19:57.105 --> 00:19:59.225
THE UNALOME, THE FOUR ELEMENTS

00:20:00.145 --> 00:20:01.665
Did you use ChatGPT?

00:20:02.265 --> 00:20:05.385
It said this works well for making up
with someone like you.

00:20:06.225 --> 00:20:07.385
A protection talisman.

00:20:07.465 --> 00:20:08.665
I wrote it myself.

00:20:09.985 --> 00:20:13.945
Things like this have to come
from a temple to be sacred.

00:20:14.025 --> 00:20:17.065
How would it work
if you wrote it yourself?

00:20:17.145 --> 00:20:18.265
Then don't take it.

00:20:18.345 --> 00:20:19.665
I'll take it.

00:20:23.865 --> 00:20:25.465
Everyone, gather up.

00:20:28.825 --> 00:20:31.505
Let's split into two teams,
like we discussed.

00:20:31.585 --> 00:20:32.465
Yes.

00:20:32.545 --> 00:20:36.465
Team One, Kamin and I will clear
these areas on the first floor.

00:20:36.545 --> 00:20:38.225
Team Two, Jade, Yu, and Lee

00:20:38.305 --> 00:20:39.785
will clear the second floor
in these areas.

00:20:40.385 --> 00:20:42.385
- Is everyone ready?
- Move out.

00:20:44.225 --> 00:20:45.305
Let's go.

00:20:47.145 --> 00:20:48.305
Be careful.

00:21:09.185 --> 00:21:10.465
Hey! Stop right there!

00:21:11.745 --> 00:21:12.985
Hey.

00:21:13.065 --> 00:21:15.345
- Hey!
- Hey, Jade! Don't go alone!

00:21:21.225 --> 00:21:22.225
Where is Jade?

00:21:22.305 --> 00:21:23.585
He chased Seon Jae downstairs by himself.

00:21:28.145 --> 00:21:29.585
Hey, don't run!

00:21:29.665 --> 00:21:30.865
Damn!

00:21:32.105 --> 00:21:33.105
Damn it! Don't run!

00:21:36.345 --> 00:21:37.465
Shit!

00:22:19.345 --> 00:22:21.145
You rammed your car into me last time.

00:22:21.945 --> 00:22:23.305
Time for payback.

00:23:07.385 --> 00:23:08.305
Hey, are you okay?

00:23:17.945 --> 00:23:19.305
Hey!

00:23:39.785 --> 00:23:42.265
Your talisman didn't help at all.

00:23:42.345 --> 00:23:44.385
I guess you need more practice.

00:23:46.345 --> 00:23:47.985
Then give it to me.

00:23:48.065 --> 00:23:49.225
I'll burn it.

00:23:49.305 --> 00:23:50.345
Burn it?

00:23:50.425 --> 00:23:51.305
Hand it over.

00:23:51.385 --> 00:23:52.505
It's okay.

00:23:54.105 --> 00:23:57.105
Honestly, if I didn't have this talisman,

00:23:58.265 --> 00:24:00.305
I might've been stabbed clean through.

00:24:00.385 --> 00:24:03.025
Then why didn't you stay in the hospital

00:24:03.105 --> 00:24:04.545
like the doctor said?

00:24:06.145 --> 00:24:07.785
I don't like hospitals.

00:24:08.585 --> 00:24:10.465
I'd rather rest at home.

00:24:12.865 --> 00:24:15.945
You talk like you'll actually rest
once you're home.

00:24:20.545 --> 00:24:22.705
Commander Don will probably call you in
for questioning soon.

00:24:22.785 --> 00:24:24.505
It's your gun.

00:24:28.505 --> 00:24:29.865
That's fine.

00:24:31.585 --> 00:24:33.025
I'll talk to the higher-ups myself.

00:24:33.945 --> 00:24:36.345
I'll tell them I was the one who fired it,

00:24:36.425 --> 00:24:38.065
not you.

00:24:38.145 --> 00:24:41.505
I think it's better
to just tell the truth.

00:24:43.105 --> 00:24:44.785
Who knows?

00:24:44.865 --> 00:24:48.425
You might even get a new subordinate
who's better than me.

00:24:48.505 --> 00:24:53.545
I believe you did it
to keep everyone safe.

00:24:56.825 --> 00:24:57.905
No.

00:24:58.865 --> 00:25:00.705
I did it

00:25:01.745 --> 00:25:03.425
to protect you.

00:25:05.865 --> 00:25:08.065
And whatever the outcome is,

00:25:09.345 --> 00:25:11.185
I'm ready to accept it.

00:25:14.265 --> 00:25:15.905
It's better than losing you.

00:26:00.825 --> 00:26:02.185
Ouch!

00:26:06.225 --> 00:26:07.145
Are you okay?

00:26:12.145 --> 00:26:13.985
I shouldn't have rushed you back.

00:26:17.225 --> 00:26:19.505
Staying in the hospital means
sleeping alone.

00:26:23.425 --> 00:26:25.185
I don't get to look at your face.

00:26:32.345 --> 00:26:33.825
Is that your only reason?

00:26:35.305 --> 00:26:37.185
That's total nonsense.

00:26:40.345 --> 00:26:42.025
When it comes to the heart,

00:26:43.265 --> 00:26:45.185
there's no such thing as nonsense.

00:27:04.345 --> 00:27:06.145
Didn't you say your wound hurts?

00:27:08.145 --> 00:27:09.705
I like it like this.

00:27:10.625 --> 00:27:11.985
Stop messing around.

00:27:12.065 --> 00:27:13.465
Go to sleep.

00:27:13.545 --> 00:27:15.145
How can you sleep like this?

00:27:25.865 --> 00:27:27.145
Good night.

00:27:49.745 --> 00:27:52.585
{\an8}I told you. Let me do it.

00:27:52.665 --> 00:27:54.065
{\an8}See?

00:27:54.625 --> 00:27:55.625
{\an8}You always…

00:27:55.705 --> 00:27:56.985
{\an8}Hey, come here.

00:27:59.265 --> 00:28:00.785
{\an8}I told you.

00:28:01.465 --> 00:28:03.745
It looks like those two have made up.

00:28:05.465 --> 00:28:07.065
They're much cuter like this.

00:28:07.905 --> 00:28:10.425
{\an8}I checked Seon Jae's phone.

00:28:10.505 --> 00:28:13.385
{\an8}Champ and Seon Jae did have a drug deal,

00:28:14.865 --> 00:28:19.505
but the drug Champ bought was ecstasy,
not ketamine like the killer used.

00:28:20.265 --> 00:28:21.785
How is that possible?

00:28:21.865 --> 00:28:24.465
Also, based on their conversation,

00:28:24.545 --> 00:28:28.305
it seems Champ and Seon Jae
only dealt with each other once.

00:28:30.585 --> 00:28:33.025
So everything we've done so far
was for nothing?

00:28:33.105 --> 00:28:35.185
Not yet. There's still hope.

00:28:35.265 --> 00:28:36.185
Here.

00:28:37.425 --> 00:28:43.145
Manmai tracked the location where
ketamine buyers met Seon Jae's people.

00:28:43.225 --> 00:28:46.025
Every time, it was this place.

00:28:46.105 --> 00:28:47.425
Where?

00:28:54.745 --> 00:28:56.225
Tonkla's dorm.

00:29:07.385 --> 00:29:09.385
But Tonkla's already dead.

00:29:09.465 --> 00:29:11.625
He can't be a suspect anymore.

00:29:11.705 --> 00:29:12.625
Exactly.

00:29:12.705 --> 00:29:14.585
But it can't be a coincidence.

00:29:14.665 --> 00:29:16.305
There has to be a connection.

00:29:20.265 --> 00:29:22.185
Hello, Dr. Puth.

00:29:22.265 --> 00:29:23.385
Hello.

00:29:24.065 --> 00:29:25.545
You came all the way here?

00:29:26.785 --> 00:29:31.105
I lost your number,

00:29:31.185 --> 00:29:33.105
so I didn't know how to report this.

00:29:33.785 --> 00:29:35.385
So I took the liberty of coming here.

00:29:37.585 --> 00:29:39.905
The toxicology result is out.

00:29:41.585 --> 00:29:44.825
No ketamine was found in Puifai's body.

00:29:46.225 --> 00:29:47.185
None at all?

00:29:47.865 --> 00:29:49.185
That's very strange.

00:29:50.025 --> 00:29:53.665
The bodies of Tar, Tonkla, Bell, and Time

00:29:55.145 --> 00:29:57.385
all had the same substance.

00:29:58.105 --> 00:30:00.145
This is the result I got.

00:30:01.105 --> 00:30:02.785
There's nothing I can do about it.

00:30:04.025 --> 00:30:06.865
I'll excuse myself now.

00:30:07.545 --> 00:30:08.905
Dr. Puth.

00:30:10.225 --> 00:30:13.985
Would it be possible to transfer
Puifai's body to the main hospital?

00:30:14.065 --> 00:30:16.145
We want to line up all five bodies

00:30:16.225 --> 00:30:18.745
to trace the killer's timeline.

00:30:21.905 --> 00:30:22.825
Is that possible?

00:30:23.865 --> 00:30:25.185
Of course.

00:30:25.865 --> 00:30:27.625
I'll arrange it.

00:30:27.705 --> 00:30:28.785
Thank you.

00:30:59.625 --> 00:31:01.145
What's wrong?

00:31:01.665 --> 00:31:02.985
Are you worried?

00:31:04.305 --> 00:31:05.905
Yeah.

00:31:07.665 --> 00:31:12.265
Will we still get to study in the UK
like we planned?

00:31:16.385 --> 00:31:18.345
Once everything's settled,

00:31:18.905 --> 00:31:20.825
wherever you want to go,

00:31:20.905 --> 00:31:22.465
whatever you want to do,

00:31:23.145 --> 00:31:24.305
I'll take you there.

00:31:27.585 --> 00:31:29.265
You're sweet.

00:31:29.905 --> 00:31:31.865
Just sweet words?

00:31:31.945 --> 00:31:33.465
What about everything else?

00:31:34.505 --> 00:31:36.825
Hey, stop it.

00:31:37.545 --> 00:31:38.785
Why?

00:31:46.305 --> 00:31:47.185
I'm going to shower first.

00:31:47.265 --> 00:31:49.225
- Need my help?
- No.

00:31:50.545 --> 00:31:53.425
Just play games. I'll be back.

00:31:53.505 --> 00:31:55.505
Hurry up. I miss you already.

00:32:40.305 --> 00:32:41.745
DRUG CHERREEN AND BRING HER
TO THE LOCATION I SENT

00:32:41.825 --> 00:32:43.345
DON'T LET ANYONE KNOW AND YOU'LL SURVIVE

00:33:28.905 --> 00:33:31.265
Are you the inspector
in charge of this case?

00:33:31.865 --> 00:33:33.425
Please calm down, sir.

00:33:33.505 --> 00:33:36.065
What the media reported is factual.

00:33:36.905 --> 00:33:38.465
And I don't have
to take responsibility for that.

00:33:39.105 --> 00:33:42.345
Even if the result shows
it's not connected to the murder case,

00:33:42.425 --> 00:33:44.225
Champ bought drugs, and that's a fact.

00:33:44.305 --> 00:33:46.185
Did you give Champ a chance to speak?

00:33:46.265 --> 00:33:50.225
Your people are the ones
obstructing police work.

00:33:51.585 --> 00:33:53.105
Inspector Kamin,

00:33:53.185 --> 00:33:55.425
do you know who you're talking to?

00:33:55.505 --> 00:33:57.385
I'm doing my duty.

00:34:01.705 --> 00:34:03.945
If Champ and you
don't cooperate with the police,

00:34:04.025 --> 00:34:06.025
Champ will be in danger.

00:34:06.105 --> 00:34:07.825
And if he ends up dead,

00:34:08.784 --> 00:34:10.304
I won't be able to protect him.

00:34:12.665 --> 00:34:14.225
Or maybe…

00:34:17.505 --> 00:34:18.824
your son is the killer.

00:34:18.905 --> 00:34:20.185
You bastard!

00:34:20.705 --> 00:34:22.905
I'll continue investigating the drugs.

00:34:22.985 --> 00:34:27.025
Besides ecstasy, there may be a history
of ketamine transactions too.

00:34:27.105 --> 00:34:28.865
How do you train your subordinates?

00:34:28.945 --> 00:34:30.425
Teaching them to frame innocent people?

00:34:30.505 --> 00:34:32.185
What kind of police force is this?

00:34:33.185 --> 00:34:34.465
I apologize, sir.

00:34:36.185 --> 00:34:38.665
I'll handle this myself.

00:34:38.744 --> 00:34:40.505
How will you handle it?

00:34:40.585 --> 00:34:42.545
One kid after another is dead.

00:34:42.625 --> 00:34:44.225
I've followed the proper procedure
in every step.

00:34:44.304 --> 00:34:45.665
Inspector!

00:34:48.505 --> 00:34:52.744
Someone foreign-educated like you
doesn't belong here.

00:34:53.824 --> 00:34:57.465
You'll be investigated for
Seon Jae's extrajudicial killing anyway.

00:34:58.305 --> 00:34:59.985
I suggest you step away from this case.

00:35:04.865 --> 00:35:07.145
Hand over your gun and badge.

00:35:07.865 --> 00:35:10.025
You're suspended indefinitely.

00:36:00.545 --> 00:36:03.385
Hey, are you okay?

00:36:03.905 --> 00:36:05.425
What?

00:36:06.905 --> 00:36:08.265
Did he hurt you?

00:36:08.785 --> 00:36:11.145
- Damn it, that commander!
- Jade, don't.

00:36:15.145 --> 00:36:19.025
The important thing for you now
is not getting fired.

00:36:20.225 --> 00:36:22.705
Otherwise, there'll be no one left
working on this case.

00:36:25.265 --> 00:36:28.905
And we still have to find
Champ and Cherreen,

00:36:29.745 --> 00:36:31.625
whether it's for the investigation

00:36:34.105 --> 00:36:35.985
or to protect them.

00:36:47.145 --> 00:36:48.465
I'm sorry.

00:36:51.185 --> 00:36:52.705
This is because of me, right?

00:37:05.665 --> 00:37:07.225
Don't say that.

00:37:12.025 --> 00:37:13.625
I'm just suspended.

00:37:16.785 --> 00:37:19.145
Think of it as a chance for me to reset.

00:37:21.905 --> 00:37:23.825
No matter what,

00:37:25.745 --> 00:37:27.505
I believe the two of us won't lose.

00:38:35.905 --> 00:38:40.345
Hey, you're not helping at all,
and you're making a mess while eating.

00:38:42.985 --> 00:38:46.265
I told you to hire someone to fix it.

00:38:46.985 --> 00:38:48.545
Why are you doing it yourself?

00:38:52.905 --> 00:38:54.825
I'm free today.

00:38:54.905 --> 00:38:56.465
I don't know what to do.

00:38:59.065 --> 00:39:00.665
You're making a mess.

00:39:02.105 --> 00:39:03.865
It's only been one day off.

00:39:03.945 --> 00:39:06.065
You don't have to do anything.

00:39:06.145 --> 00:39:07.585
Get some rest.

00:39:12.705 --> 00:39:13.745
Hey, your mouth's messy.

00:39:16.985 --> 00:39:19.145
Go tidy up the house now.

00:39:20.665 --> 00:39:22.305
Start with that corner.

00:39:25.705 --> 00:39:26.905
Seriously?

00:39:27.425 --> 00:39:28.265
Of course.

00:39:33.305 --> 00:39:34.825
Come on, tidy it up.

00:39:35.385 --> 00:39:36.265
Hurry.

00:39:36.865 --> 00:39:38.305
What's with you?

00:39:39.905 --> 00:39:41.785
Do it properly. Faster.

00:39:46.105 --> 00:39:48.425
I'm not your dad, you know.

00:39:48.505 --> 00:39:50.585
I don't have to clean up after you.

00:39:50.665 --> 00:39:53.065
I know you're not my dad,

00:39:53.145 --> 00:39:54.825
but could you be
my house husband for a bit?

00:39:54.905 --> 00:39:58.105
When you're done using
the AC remote or the TV remote,

00:39:58.185 --> 00:40:00.625
put them back where they belong.
Otherwise, no one can find them.

00:40:00.705 --> 00:40:01.865
"Otherwise, no one can find them."

00:40:01.945 --> 00:40:03.505
Otherwise, no one can find them!

00:40:03.585 --> 00:40:05.145
Jeez, Inspector!

00:40:07.465 --> 00:40:09.185
Go back to work already.

00:40:09.265 --> 00:40:12.905
If I let you do housework like this,
I'll die first.

00:40:12.985 --> 00:40:14.345
Captain, I--

00:40:24.425 --> 00:40:26.585
Fine. I'll be your dad for a day then.

00:40:38.905 --> 00:40:41.185
Based on the forensic team's analysis
of Seon Jae's phone,

00:40:41.265 --> 00:40:43.345
we've identified a meetup location.

00:40:43.425 --> 00:40:44.545
It's near Tonkla's dorm.

00:40:44.625 --> 00:40:46.065
I'll check it out myself.

00:40:46.145 --> 00:40:48.425
They've been smuggling chemical substances
out of the hospital

00:40:49.185 --> 00:40:50.425
and exchanging them here.

00:40:50.505 --> 00:40:51.865
It's the hospital where Dr. Puth works.

00:40:57.785 --> 00:40:58.745
From now on,

00:40:58.825 --> 00:41:01.145
the commander will probably
be watching the two of us more closely.

00:41:01.225 --> 00:41:02.305
We may need to keep some distance.

00:41:02.385 --> 00:41:04.105
Then I'll go back to being your superior.

00:41:04.185 --> 00:41:07.625
This is an order. Not from your superior,
but from your boyfriend.

00:41:08.465 --> 00:41:11.385
Roger that, Inspector Kamin,
Captain Jade's boyfriend.

00:41:11.465 --> 00:41:13.585
Yes, Captain Jade,

00:41:14.985 --> 00:41:16.465
Inspector Kamin's boyfriend.